Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt, after Bourdon; the Virgin and Child seated in centre foreground; an angel kneeling at left kissing the child's hand; at right St Elizabeth with the Infant Baptist and another two angels; landscape background with women washing clothes in a river in front of a fortified town and St Joseph with the ass at left Etching and engraving
Producer name: Published by: François de Poilly I
Curator's comments: The second state lettered: 'Seb. Bourdon Pinx. E. Hainzelman sculpt.' After Bourdon's tondo now in Dijon. See Jacques Thuillier, 'Sébastien Bourdon 1616-1671', Paris 2000, cat. 275.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / German engravings, etchings and woodcuts c.1400-1700 (12.I)
Associated names: Representation of: St John the Baptist (Prodromos)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Nan Ino Cooper, Baroness Lucas of Crudwell and Lady Dingwall
In Memory of: Auberon Thomas Herbert, 9th Baron Lucas of Crudwell and 5th Lord Dingwall
